chic place away from the city's hustle bustle yet one toto ride to everywhere. Perfect for people needing to crash somewhere for a night in Siliguri before their train/flight

This cozy room was a pleasant and comfortable place to stay. Away from the messy downtown area of Siliguri, but just near to the Station Feeder Rd, this quaint slice of Saktigarh strikes a nice balance of peace and outing options.
The room itself is small but equipped with all amenities you could need for a short stay - working Wi-Fi, AC, geyser, smart TV. Lots of windows with a view of the sunset straight from the bed was a nice cherry on top. Suman and Sonia were responsive and easy to communicate with. All in all, a well-recommended stay in Siliguri.
The host was very helpful
It was a good resting place.

The place was just as described. It was located away from the busy roads and it was just as I needed after a week long hectic activity. The room was clean and welcoming. The washroom was spacious and clean as well. It had a functional AC and a ceiling fan too. I had a very good sleep and the host also was very kind enough to arrange the transport to the airport. They kept following up with me and was patient enough when I had a late check in.
I would love to stay here again in the future. Place is 15kms away from the airport and can be reached in 30-40mins.
We had our breakfast at Makhan Bhog which is 15mins walk from the stay.

a good place to halt n take a break between traveling dates.

Beautiful cozy place.

We stayed at Suman's place after arriving from Darjeeling. Initially, we had difficulty finding transportation as local drivers were hesitant to come to our location. The bathroom flush wasn't working, and the bedsheets were dirty with hair and fur. Additionally, the area was noisy at night due to hooligans and stray dogs. Uber and Ola was unavailable to go to airport the next day.
Suman was helpful in sharing the location, but we were unsure why auto drivers were not coming. Overall, our experience was okay, but these issues affected our stay.

Nice stay, Suman hosted me 3 times,
Highly recommended.

Great host, welcomed nicely, communication was clear,
overall a great stay.
Best part is proactive host response and flexible checkin and checkout time. Ok for 1 night stay for 1-2 people. Commode flush was not working and the the cover also was completely comings down.
The overall stay was good and safe ! Few amenities need repairs - area wise looked safe!
Great place. Great host. Amazing.
It was a cozy stay at the lookout. Aunty was very cooperative whenever we needed anything. Looking forward to staying there again.

The place is reachable. Have good amenities for the price. Host is very accommodating.
We had some some special requirements for which we didn't rate 5 star.
1. Parking was on street which was a little narrow, so I was a little concerned entire night.
2. I am a pet owner and the neighborhood had lots of dog and few of them were not so calm, so if you plan to stay with your pet then better to keep the pet always inside. this becomes an issue for any pet owner for the potty and peeing of the pets.
other than this the accomodation was very nice for the price it's been offered.

Had booked Suman’s place for my night stay during my road trip. Shared a great deal of life’s journey while talking to Suman. He had shared the necessary navigation to his place well in advance, and helped me in arranging dinner for my stay. Appreciate their courtesy in helping me check out early for my upcoming travel plans.
A cozy apartment equipped with all necessary facilities, my stay was wonderful.
worth what I paid for
It was a pleasant stay with Suman and he has been a very great host. I would definitely recommend his house if you are in Siliguri.
